<dl id="n41057a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n41" href="#n41057a">N41 (VI.B.33)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n41all.htm#n41057a"> 57(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font><span class="strike"><span class="striketext">angel</span></span> man<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> takes off overcoat / &amp; is angel</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Wherefore also after death when he <font color="green">[man]</font> <mark>puts off his externals</mark> which he had derived from the natural world, <mark>he becomes a spirit or an angel</mark>. <small> Emanuel Swedenborg, <a name="ESAW" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ESAW"><cite title="source">Angelic Wisdom Concerning the Divine Love</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 129</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
